deck_excerpt: Fallen of Kashtira V2Yu-Gi-Oh! Deck Uploaded by ZombiePuke
deck_description: A deck automatically uploaded from the Master Duel Companion App to YGOPRODeck.com. Our companion app offers a Yu-Gi-Oh! Master Duel deck tracker to assist players in tracking their deck and stats. Try it here!

A deck automatically uploaded from the Master Duel Companion App to YGOPRODeck.com. Our companion app offers a Yu-Gi-Oh! Master Duel deck tracker to assist players in tracking their deck and stats. Try it here!
Let me know how it went, success or flaws, haven't tried it but by theory, it should be good.

Naturia Control with Fusion Toolbox

This deck focuses on controlling the duel through disruption and resource management, while utilizing the "Naturia" archetype for advantage and summoning powerful Fusion Monsters.

Monsters (21):

  • Naturia Engine (13): This core group consists of various "Naturia" monsters that benefit each other. "Naturia Beast" allows searching for other "Naturia" cards, while "Naturia Camellia" recycles banished "Naturia" monsters. The deck uses a playset of "Naturia Mole Cricket" for its hand-trapping effect and swarming potential.
  • Hand Traps (6): The deck employs staples like "Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring" and "Effect Veiler" to disrupt your opponent's plays. "Ghost Ogre & Snow Rabbit" targets monsters with effects when they activate.
  • Searchers (3): "One for One" and "Lonefire Blossom" help search for specific monsters, while "Spore" can be used to bring out "Naturia Beast."
  • Other (2): "Rose Lover" offers revival for Plant monsters, and "Snowdrop the Rikka Fairy" provides some searching utility.

Spells (17):

  • Draw Power (2): "Pot of Prosperity" fuels your hand advantage, while "Foolish Burial" sets up graveyard effects for monsters like "Naturia Exterio."
  • Disruption (4): "Called by the Grave" removes threats from your opponent's graveyard, while "Super Polymerization" allows for powerful Fusion Summons using monsters on both sides of the field. "Solemn Judgment" negates powerful effects.
  • Naturia Support (3): "Naturia Blessing" offers protection and search for "Naturia" monsters.
  • Utility (8): "Waking the Dragon" revives a Level 5 or higher monster, "Naturia Sacred Tree" provides additional resources, and "One for One" helps search for specific monsters.

Traps (2): None in this build, focusing on proactive strategies.

Extra Deck (15):

  • Naturia Fusions (3): "Naturia Exterio" is a powerful boss monster, while "Naturia Barkion" and "Naturia Beast" offer additional control and swarming options.
  • Generic Fusions (7): "Starving Venom Fusion Dragon" steals ATK, "Predaplant Dragostapelia" negates effects, and "Mudragon of the Swamp" provides removal. The deck also includes "Psychic End Punisher" for piercing damage, two copies of "Trishula" for negation and removal, and "Draco Berserker of the Tenyi" for a strong beatstick.
  • Other (5): "Black Rose Dragon" offers board clearing, "Teardrop the Rikka Queen" searches for Plant monsters, "Aromaseraphy Jasmine" negates effects, and "S:P Little Knight" provides a Link Summoning option.

Overall Strategy:

This deck aims to disrupt your opponent's plays with hand traps and "Called by the Grave" while building advantage through the "Naturia" engine and card draw. You can then use "Super Polymerization" to create powerful Fusion Monsters like "Naturia Exterio" to take control of the duel. The versatile toolbox Extra Deck offers options for various situations.
One sheep, two sheep, many more sheep.

Exodia Obliterate - Draw Solo Minigame Project

The rules are simple, be able to pull the 5 pieces of the forbidden in the first 2 turns.
Theres 2 levels/formats to play:

> TCG legal format:
All cards are tournament legal.
Switching between Morphing Jar & Card Destruction to Pot of Avarice & Pot of Duality for less opponent hand interaction or adding Triple Tactics for a more tournament approach.

> Not Legal Solo Minigame:  
The rules change, now you have to pull an OTK, if you brick you lose.
Replace the next cards:
Cup of Ace x2 - Pot of Greed x2
Gold Sarcophagus - Pot of Greed, Pot of Duality or Pot of Avarice
Monster Rencarnation - Graceful Charity

deck_excerpt: Those who call the Sanctuary in the Sky home do not like visitors. Show those trespassers the divine wrath of angels.
deck_description:
So, this is a deck for a format called Domain! Rules of deckbuilding are simple, for those unaware.

1. 60 card main, 15 card extra deck, singleton, no banlist.
2. I can use any spells and traps I desire, however I can only use cards that fit my "Deckmaster's Domain", in this case my Deckmaster is the Harest Angel Of Doom (Hence it being in my sideboard). Domain consists of all cards of the Deckmaster's attribute, type, any archetypes listed in their name, as well as any attributes, types, archetypes, and exact statlines listed in the Deckmaster's text, with the exclusion of reminder text (aside from archetypal, like summoned skull being an archfiend).

In this case, I can use any dark monster, and any fairy monster. So, I decided to go with Sanctuary In The Sky, a mix of Counter Fairies, Parshath, and The Agents! I want opinions on this. Also, the Barian's Chaos Draw is really supposed to be a Seventh Tachyon, but it wasn't on here when I moved the deck in.

Goal is simple. Control the board, and beat face while they have nothing. More difficult as this is singleton and against 3 other people, but that's what I like about this deck- the challenge. Plus, it makes Iron Thunder hilarious due to the way collumns work in Domain, hehe.

deck_name: Winged Dragon of Ra- Ogdoadic- Horus 100% (never bricks)
deck_excerpt: Winged Dragon of Ra- Ogdoadic- Horus 100% (never bricks)
deck_description:
Winged Dragon of Ra 100% (never bricks)

My favorite card of all time, the one that got me into yugioh, was the Winged Dragon of Ra. It got me to try master duel, and start my whole journey. 

My second favorite archetype was Ogdoadic, because I raise and care for reptiles, and the just looked like the would go perfectly with Ra. I was able to make a deck with Bishbaalkin, the one from DarkArmedDuelists channel, that essentially let me add Slifer and Ra, and use them pretty consistantly without having to normal summon. But once Bishbaalkin was banned that deck was no longer usable on masterduel. I was no longer able to use both in a useable way. In comes Horus (which Horus himself looks like Ra). It lets us increase our starters and get maximum consistancy.

HOW THE DECK WORKS

Deck Breakdown:

12 starters:
Ogdoadic: 3x Nunu, 3x Nauya
Horus: 3x Imsety, 3x King's Sacophagus

9 Conditional starters/extenders:
Ogdoadic: 3x Ogdoadic daybreak, 1x Ogdoadic Serpent Strike, 1x Ogdoadic Water Lily, 1x Zohah
Reptile: 1x Black Mamba, 1x Night Sword Serpent, 1x I.A.S. Invasive Alien Species

9 Bricks (extenders when sent to graveyard, often with Horus engine):
2x Guardian Slime, The Ogdoadic Light & Dark, Both Ogdoadic Overlords, Blessing, Protection and Guidance of Horus

10 Ra Summons/Seachers:
2x Winged Dragon of Ra, 2x Sphere Mode, 3x Ancient Chant, 3x The True Sun God

Exta deck:
Necassary: Fera Imps is needed for the Nunu 1 card combo
Conditional:
-Galaxy-eyes cards optional, 2 card destroyed on the field, change of heart that can be used as material for rank up, protection for light monsters, or an omni-negate.
-Number 97 engine and Nummeron Dragon optional, just for OTK if you dont get Ra, a spell negate, or defense piercing dmg
-Alien Shocktrooper and Cosmic Slicer, optional, especially if you go first, and can get lots of tokens on the field, it  basically negates all on field opponent monsters and changes them to defense position, if you add alien kid to the deck and swap it out with one of the non Ogdoadic Reptile cards.
-Lizadose Optional, banish reptile from gy draw one
-Echidina Optional, makes an opponents monster 0 atk, good for OTK

Goal of the Deck:
To get Ra on the field going 2nd with a 6 card hand basically every single hand in a digitially shuffled or a well in person shuffled deck. I have tested 20 hands and was always able to either get Ra on the field, or  3/20 instances go into Nummeron Dragon or Galaxy-Eyes Dragon. The following figures are based upon the Yugioh Probability Calculator.

Basically we have 12 starters that can each individually get 3 bodies on the field for Ra, as a 1 card combo(nunu is the only one that would require using a normal summon to get 3 monsters on the field, the other 9 require no normal summons), and combined with the 9 situational starters (situation being 1 normal summonable reptile monster), we are going to have about 92.93% chance to open with 2 of any of these 21 cards. 
But if we just want to concider the 12 starters, we have a 90.18% chance to draw at least 1 of them.

With 10 Ra cards, we have a 84.53% chance to draw at least 1 Ra card. (Im not counting Guardian Slime which is classified as a brick/conditional extender, but if we include it, it rises to 90.18%)

With 9 Brick/Conditional Extender Cards, we have a 80.82% chance to draw at least 1, 40.98% chance to draw at least 2, and an 11.47% chance to draw at least 3, and an 1.63% to drawing at least 4. 

Basically you are competing against a very small likelyhood you would draw 3 or 4 bricks, and there is an exremely high likelyhood you will draw at least 1 one card combo starter, and a Ra/Searcher. (If you add 3 Ashes and 3 Maxx C, for 46 cards, it lowers the chance to pull 1 one card starter combo by 5%, so it goes from 90% to 85%)

trying to play an almost unplayable archetype! The fairies actually make the deck worse but they were the only reason i made this deck.
The combo starts with lady past and light on the field (you can summon, one for one, hikari or fortune visions -> lady calling them).
Activate past's effect to increase her level, using light. Activate light's effect to summon lady water, synchro summon 999 times charge warrior and catastor with desynchro for bootleg pot of greed. You should end up with zoroa, a 2/3 monsters apo if you manage to hold calling and a bunch of useless shit. Half of the deck (dangers/magicians soul) is used to draw stuff, to get free bodies and to recycle the useless crap in hand.
If you manage to summon 2 pasts, you can also end up with crystal wing and hatsune miku in the graveyard!
